[282.821639, "o", "\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[G\r\n\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mвҸә\u001b[39m Perfect! I've successfully rearranged the skeets page with the following changes:\r\n\r\n  1. \u001b[1mCreated a new \u001b[38;5;153mSkeetCard\u001b[39m component\u001b[22m (\u001b[38;5;153mlib/nathan_for_us_web/components/skeet_card.ex\u001b[39m) that encapsulates all the\r\n  post card logic from the original file\r\n  2. \u001b[1mUpdated the layout\u001b[22m to use a responsive CSS Grid mosaic with:\r\n    - 1 column on mobile\r\n    - 2 columns on small screens\r\n    - 3 columns on large screens\r\n    - 4 columns on extra large screens (max 4 per row as requested)\r\n  3. \u001b[1mEnhanced the card design\u001b[22m with:\r\n    - Better hover effects and transitions\r\n    - Improved spacing and typography\r\n    - More compact elements for better mosaic display\r\n    - Rounded avatars and optimized image sizes\r\n    - Better responsive behavior\r\n\r\n  The new layout creates a visually appealing \"hodge podge\" of posts that's easy to read while maximizing the\r\n  number of v"]
